President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation on May 15, 2020, in honor of Armed Forces Day. The proclamation pays tribute to the men and women of the United States Armed Forces who serve with honor and distinction, defending the nation in times of war and peace. It recognizes the historical accomplishments of the Armed Forces, including the recent 75th anniversary of Victory in Europe Day, and highlights their current efforts in the fight against the coronavirus pandemic. The proclamation emphasizes the commitment of the administration to provide the military with necessary training and equipment, with a historic $2.2 trillion investment in the military since President Trump took office. It also celebrates the creation of the United States Space Force as a response to evolving threats in the 21st-century world. The proclamation invites governors and organizations to observe Armed Forces Day and encourages all Americans to display the flag of the United States at their homes and businesses.